Reasoning: The paper proposes a computational approach to solve the synergistic team composition problem (STCP) in co-operative learning, which involves partitioning a set of individuals into diverse teams based on competencies, personality, and gender. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for developing algorithms to solve the STCP, machine learning (cs.LG) for learning team performance models, computational complexity (cs.CC) for analyzing the computational properties of the proposed algorithms, social and information networks (cs.SI) for studying the social dynamics of team formation, and computer education (cs.CE) for applying the STCP in educational contexts.
